      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "POWER TO RULE (1) led and bolted in at York last time out when breaking his maiden in emphatic fashion. He was 1100 to 1500m there and steps up again to 1660m The claim of Catarino is a big tick and he's likely to take up the running once again. Can repeat the dose. MISSIJAY (7) will find this much easier than what she's been racing in recently, tackling a $40k event at Albany last time. Right back in grade now and she has enough early speed to work across from the tricky gate. Can play a leading role. MR HOLLYWOOD (2) showed good early dash before weakening to be beaten 6L over 1920m at York last time out. Worth another chance. HOT CHATTER (5) finished well back on turf at Mt Barker two starts back. Missed the frame in another run on turf last time at York over 1920m when 6L adrift in tenth. Sound claims on her return to the dirt. ANYTIME ANYWHERE (3) has claims.",
